How to integrate with your protocol

Your main contract (e.g., Catalyst) just implements the callback:

function onDRSRecover(bytes32 role, address /*oldAccount*/, address newAccount) external {
    require(msg.sender == address(council), "only council");
    if (role == keccak256("DEPLOYER")) {
        deployerAddress = newAccount; // or update fee receiver
    } else if (role == keccak256("ADMIN")) {
        _grantRole(DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE, newAccount);
        // optionally revoke compromised admin in same tx
    } else {
        // custom roles if needed
    }
}

Point TARGET to your contract.

Set ROLE to keccak256("DEPLOYER") or keccak256("ADMIN").

For DRS v2, initialize Batch A and Batch B with different guardian sets. Your DAO (manager) can refill the locked batch any time.
